Question: Many universities require that freshman live on campus dorm during the first year of college. In your opinion, is this a good or a bad thing? Explain your opinion on this issue.
Answer:
I would say it is very good for freshman to live on campus. If you are not going to the university in your hometown, it always takes a while to get familiar with the city. Living on campus will help them to get better access of everything and informed of what is happening in school.